Build a Local eCommerce Website Using XAMPP and WordPres
1.    Download XAMPP:
    -Visit the official XAMPP website and download the version for your operating system.
    -Install and configure XAMPP on your PC.
2.    Download WordPress:
    -Go to the WordPress website and download the latest version.
    -Extract the WordPress files into the htdocs folder of your XAMPP installation.
3.    Set Up a Local Website:
    -Start Apache and MySQL services using the XAMPP control panel.
    -Use phpMyAdmin to create a database for your WordPress site.
    -Install WordPress by visiting http://localhost/your-folder-name in your browser.
    -Complete the installation process by setting up a site title and admin credentials.
4.Build an eCommerce Website:
   - Install the WooCommerce plugin from the WordPress dashboard.
    -Configure WooCommerce with basic settings:
        -Add a store name, currency, and location.
        -Set up at least one payment method (example: "Cash on Delivery").
    -Add at least 3 Categories and each category has 5 products to the store, including images, descriptions, prices, and categories.
    Create the following pages:
    Homepage showcasing featured products.
    Shop Page listing all products.
    Cart Page for customers to view selected items.
    About Page for customers to view about company profile.
    Contact Page with basic store information.
